column_.text_: This city is huge...
There's stuff everywhere!

Welcome. This is Zegagrande Skydom's largest city,
Seedhollow.
Phew. The good news is the Grandcypher's gonna be okay.

She's in good hands. Luckily the ship escaped severe damage.
Should be a quick fix.
Sorry to keep pilin' stuff on you. 'Preciate it, buddy.

So about this Family Zathba or whatever. You know where to find
'em?
I sure do. Their boss supposedly operates in this district.

Information brokers don't exactly advertise to the public. He runs a
bar as a front.
Sounds like he's got his stuff together.
I guess you'll find out for yourself when you meet him. Follow me!

Let's start by heading to the main square. The bar should be
in a back alley somewhere.
Guess we oughta start checkin' the backstreets, huh?

Huh, guess that's one way to design a ship. Always cool to
see how other places build their rides.

Wait till you visit the other districts. I'd love to give a grand
tour, but...

No biggie. Besides, sightseeing'll be a lot more fun once
Lyria's back with us.
Very true. I'd better start brushing up on my tour guide skills.
Judging from your gear, are you perhaps skyfarers?
Welcome! This is Rafale's Seedhollow branch.

Of course, Seedhollow wouldn't be complete without a
blacksmith and Alliance rep.
If you need to use their services, now's the time.

They've got all kinds of flowers here. No wonder the city
smells so good.
I guess that's where the "seed" in Seedhollow comes from.
Ah, I think I've been here before...

We probably should've made an appointment. Oh well, we'll
make it work.
You're skyfarers? Sorry, you can't pass through here.

The aristocracy lives in that district. It's closed to the general
public, so let's check elsewhere.

This estate belongs to a VIP. Are we gonna have a problem
here?
N-no, no! We must've taken a wrong turn somewhere.
Check it out. This city goes all the way to the island's edge.

Yes. Each district has its own dock, which makes it easy to
get around by airship.

No way! Is that the new Nimbus-class sky liner? They're
operational here? What a beast!
What are you, ten?

You can take the man out of boyhood, but you can't take
boyhood out of the man.
Uh-huh. Whatever floats your boat.
Man, this sucks...
Totally. So much freakin' work to do.
Hm? Say, don't you two work for Zathba?
Who's askin'?

Oh snap, it's Rolan! Where you been hiding, man? 
Thanks for always lookin' out for the boss.

No, no, quite the opposite. Zathba has always been the
one bailing me out. That info on Avia was spot-on.

But enough about that. It looks like you gentlemen are in a bit of a
pickle.

A pickle? No, man. We're swamped with work right now. 
Everyone in the family's fully booked.

So if you got biz with the boss, could you maybe go chill and come
back later?
Hm... I get you're busy, but we're also on the clock here...

So what I'm hearing is, once these errands of yours are cleared out,
that'll open up Zathba's schedule. Is that right?

More or less. Not like our mountain of work is gonna get smaller
anytime soon though...

Got it. , what do you say to lending these fine 
fellows a hand?
I'm in!
Anything to help Lyria.
I'm in!
I'm in!
Me too. Beats sittin' around all day.
Anything to help Lyria.
Anything to help Lyria.

Right. We need info, and if it takes a little elbow grease, then let's
grease it up.

There you go. Meet your newest co-workers.
And not just any co-workers. These skyfarers have an
impressive résumé!
For real? Awesome. Thanks.

We appreciate it. For starters, ya think you could check in with a buddy
of ours? He should be at the market.
Let's kick some tail!
Sigh, so much for having the day off. Wish I had an assistant.
What's up, Rolan. Sorry, the boss still isn't back yet.
Yo! I got the word. Ready to roll up your sleeves?

Here's the deal. Some bigwig "lost" something in the city.
Something really dangerous.
I, uh, can't handle it myself without my legs turning to jelly.
Talk with an Alliance rep. I left the details with them.

Huh? You're looking for something dangerous? Oh, you must mean
"that."
Mm... Yeah. I know a few folks that might be able to help you out.
I'll write down what they look like. Go see what they have to say.

Why can't you just tell us what it is... Oh, whatever. Let's
move on to the next person.

You're looking for something a magnate lost? Hm... That could only
be one thing.
Yep, no doubt about it.
If it's what I think it is, you'll find it in an alley.
Wait, so the thing is alive? This is making my beard bristle.
Zathba's people have you looking for a dangerous thing?
Ah! Okay, okay. Yeah, I guess you could call it dangerous.

Try looking in places with shade. But be careful. Never know what
might jump out at you!

Raise our eyes to the blue? Um... What are you talking
about?
Skies above skies! The heavens have anointed me as their beacon!

Raise your eyes to the blue! That which you seek may come from
above.

Look in the shade... above our heads... down an alley? Is that
what they're telling us?

Maybe? Guess it's time to start crawling the backstreets of
Seedhollow.

Don't tell me that's the dangerous thing we've been looking
for...

It's just a cat! Geez, how dangerous can it be? C'mon, let's
get it home.
The client is over the moon! Phew. Glad that's over with.
You coulda just told us you can't stand cats.

When I was a kid, I got scratched by one. It left a scar on my body
and my psyche...
Aw, but you don't wanna hear about that! Thanks again!

Can't believe we went on a wild cat chase. Why would the
Family Zathba bother with boring jobs?

I believe being a good information broker means having a
finger in every pie, so to speak.

In any case, we're making good progress. On to the next
task!
My, what a magnificent castle.

Calling it huge would be an insult. Bet you could spot that
thing from the next skydom over.

It's been a fixture of this city since time immemorial. After all
these years, I still get emotional when I look at it.

Whoops, this is no time for sightseeing. We need to find
Zathba's bar.
Here to lend a hand? Couldn't have come at a better time.

We're assessing the castle's manpower, but it's not like the
guards'll volunteer to take a survey.
I hate to use the term "eavesdrop," but we're short on ears.

If you see any castle guards, could you listen in? Out of sight and
without getting caught, obviously.

Remember, keep it hush-hush. Is there anywhere we can
hide?
Who are you people? There's nothing to see here.
Uh-oh!
Zathba's subordinate was right. We have to stay out of sight.
This spot looks good for spying.
Shh!
Heard the news?
Yeah. They raised the threat level for the skydom.

If they keep sending reinforcements to Tempeal and other islands,
castle defenses will be stretched thin.

It's taking a toll on the public safety team too. The Church of Avia
has been popping up everywhere.

At least we're safe here. Don't have to worry about Seedhollow
getting invaded. Just hope I don't get shipped out.

Mobilizing soldiers out of Seedhollow is sapping the castle's
defenses. People might get edgy if this leaks.
Greetings, skyfarers. Welcome to Seedhollow.
Cheese it!
Where can we eavesdrop without being noticed?
Let's camp out here.
So my granddad said the craziest thing the other day.
Well don't leave me hanging.
You know the Corridor of Peace? Know why they really call it that?
No, why?
It's to honor an Astral who once saved us skydwellers.
Haha, that's a good one.
Pfft, what a joke.

That's what I said. They were the ones who conquered us. A
compassionate Astral... Heh, can you imagine?

Now that story I'd like to hear more about. Unfortunately, it
has nothing to do with our task.
What are you staring at?
N-nothing!
Sneaky does it now...
Ya think we can hide here?
I know what I saw...

That Harvin was wearing white robes—matched what was
described in the intel report to a tee.

They say that uniform's doled out to one of the deadliest groups in
Avia.

Obviously, the Silver Wolf Corps is also nothing to sneeze at, but
this group uses strange techniques...

Argh, I should've arrested that Harvin! What if they've already
infiltrated the city!?

Avia may have already infiltrated Seedhollow? That's bad
news, but good to know.
I think we've heard enough. Let's go report this in.
Back so soon? How'd it go?

I see. I guess we'd better offer some resources to bolster the
castle's defenses.

By the way, didn't you say something about needing to see the
boss?
He should be in by now. Why don't you head for the bar?

It's finally time to meet the legend himself. From what I've
seen with his underlings, he runs a tight ship.
Dead end. Feels like I'm in a maze.

This Zathba guy sure likes to dip his talons in everything,
huh?

Yes. Thanks to him and his informants, the city's managed to
stay relatively peaceful.

But I'm going to do him one better and protect every single
dweller in these skies.

Really? Are you sure you're not biting off more than you can
chew?
Err... Was that too much? Anyway, time to hit the bar!
Everyone, meet Zathba.
Well out with it.
That's some jam.
Yeah, I was hoping you could help—
Let's talk business.
You didn't let me finish...
We aren't a charity. Selling info is how we don't starve.
And the juicier the intel, the tastier our meals.

You want a seat at the table, you gotta bring the bread, know what
I'm saying?
Loud and clear.
So how much will it cost?
Loud and clear.
Loud and clear.
'N you folks don't strike me as the type that can afford our prices.
I'll say. Those hefty ship repair bills add up pretty darn fast.
So how much will it cost?
So how much will it cost?

Avia exposes us to huge risk. 
With the friend discount, you're looking at seven mil.
Seven million rupies?! That's enough to purchase several airships!

We settle our payments up front, but I wager your wallets are a
little bit light at the moment.

How about a proposal?
You scratch my back, and I'll scratch yours.
(We really don't have time for this...)
Heh. Don't pass on a deal till you've heard every last detail.

We've already looked into the mind sealer around your friend's
neck.

The catalyst stone that'll cancel the magic sleeps in some ruins on
Dahli Island.
Are you absolutely certain?

Lemme guess: you're givin' us the scoop 'cause you want
somethin' in return.
Heh... Man knows how to cut to the chase.

All you resourceful folks have to do is break the seal on those
ruins.

It just so happens there's hidden treasure in there we'd love to get
our hands on.

And those are the conditions. 
Not a bad deal, if you ask me.
Yep. We both get what we want. Seems fair enough.
At this point, I think any lead is worth investigating.
The choice is yours, .

I'll be waiting at the port. 
Come see me when you've got your answer.
Mr. Shades back there was no ordinary dude.
I think you painted a different picture of the guy, Rolan.
Ahaha... Well, he's... very passionate about his work, yes.
We didn't come here to dig up treasure for someone else.

I know it's not the most direct way to get to Lyria, but it's
better than nothing.

Why did it have to be Dahli Island though? Not to mention
breaking the seal on the ruins...

But if we don't take that risk... I suppose Zathba knows what
he's doing.

What're you mumblin' about? C'mon, he said he's waiting at
the port.
Dahli Island... How many years has it been?

Hurry up. Mr. Shades might cancel the offer if we take too
long.

The fruit in the market looked so good. Too bad it'll have to
wait for another day.

Yeah. Who knows when we'll find the time to kick back and
relax.
I'm sure Lyria will fall in love with this beautiful city.
It's gonna be great showing her around!
Hi, everyone! I bear good tidings!

Zathba wanted to thank you for your hardwork. Something
about finding hot gossip and shady cats?
Skyfaring work sure is something else! Enjoy your gift!
I don't got all day. We doing this or not?
Offer still stands if you're up for it.
Pleasure working with you.
I need a little more time to think.
Pleasure working with you.
Pleasure working with you.

Good. Neither of us wants a fine business opportunity to slip
through our fingers.

Hey! This is out of the blue, but I might have some personal things
to tend to...
Say what? You're gonna flake on us?

While you check the ruins, I'll look for the red ship. It'll be more
efficient.
I appreciate the thought, but should you go after them alone?

There's no need to worry about me.
I promise. I always finish what I start.
Thank you, Rolan. We owe you so much.
Take care of them, Zathba.

Are you telling me how to do my job? Who's wearing the informant
pants, here?
Haha, you got me there. What was I thinking?
Oh, but at least take this.
Well, well. A transceiver.
I made it with my own two hands. I'd like it back when this is over.
Heh. Better hope it doesn't fall apart on me then.

Now as a small bonus, our family's pride and joy will fly you to
Dahli in style.
Be careful out there, everyone!
I need a little more time to think.
I need a little more time to think.
Fine. Talk to me again once you've made up your mind.

Oh, and before you ask, this ride's free. Make it worth my
while, skyfarers.

Dahli Island. That's where we're going to find the catalyst
stone to free Lyria from the mind sealer.

Dahli Island. That's where we're going to find the catalyst
stone to free Lyria from the mind sealer.

This is our last thread of hope, and nothing's gonna make us
let go. Not even a waking nightmare.

This is our last thread of hope, and nothing's gonna make us
let go. Not even a waking nightmare.
Shh... It's okay...
Come. The stars await. And we mustn't keep them.
You were tossing. Do you feel all right?
Yeah...
And how are you feeling?
I feel fine.
Why ask me such a question?
I've found it. Another god.
